<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="103" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="103">
<taxonomicName LSID="033B05E3-A094-5F4C-9B7A-755145D2A4E7" authority="(A. Gray) Sukhor." authorityName="Sukhorukov &amp; Nilova &amp; Krinitsina &amp; Maxim A. Zaika &amp; Erst &amp; Shepherd" authorityYear="2018" baseAuthorityName="A. Gray" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Neomonolepis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Neomonolepis spathulata" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="spathulata" status="comb. nov.">Neomonolepis spathulata (A.Gray) Sukhor.</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="0" pageNumber="103">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="103" type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="103">
≡ 
<taxonomicName authority="H.A.Schrader, 1831" authorityName="A. Gray" authorityYear="1868" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Monolepis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Monolepis spathulata" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="spathulata">Monolepis spathulata</taxonomicName>
A.Gray, Proc. Amer. Acad. Arts 7: 389 (1868). Lectotype (Sukhorukov, designated here): [USA, California, Sierra Nevada], Mono Pass, 1866, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">H.N. Bolander 6373</emphasis>
lower right-hand specimen (GH00037208 [image]!, isolectotypes MO-216255 [image]! NY01085540 [image]! US00921387 [image]! YU064591 [image]!).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="103">
≡ 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Blitum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Blitum spathulatum" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="spathulatum">Blitum spathulatum</taxonomicName>
(A.Gray) S.Fuentes, Uotila et Borsch, Willdenowia 42(1): 17 (2012).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="103" type="morphological notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="103">Morphological notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="103">
As 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Neomonolepis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Neomonolepis" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">Neomonolepis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a monotypic genus, the description of 
<taxonomicName genus="N." lsidName="N. spathulata" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" rank="species" species="spathulata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">N. spathulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
corresponds to the generic description above. 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Neomonolepis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Neomonolepis spathulata" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="spathulata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">Neomonolepis spathulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically distant from all 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Neomonolepis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="tribe" tribe="Dysphanieae">Dysphanieae</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Teloxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Teloxys" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">Teloxys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Suckleya" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Suckleya" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">Suckleya</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
A.Gray, 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Dysphania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Dysphania" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">Dysphania</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
R.Br. and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Moquin-Tandon" authorityYear="1840" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Cycloloma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cycloloma" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">Cycloloma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Moq.) in being glabrous in all parts (vs. glandular and/or simple hairs), having unisexual flowers (vs. bisexual or polygamous) and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="‘stalactite’">'stalactite'</normalizedToken>
seed-coat testa (vs. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="‘non-stalactite’">'non-stalactite'</normalizedToken>
). For this reason, we prefer to refer to the clade with the above-mentioned genera as the ' 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Moquin-Tandon" authorityYear="1840" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Cycloloma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="tribe" tribe="Dysphanieae">Dysphanieae</taxonomicName>
+ 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Neomonolepis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Neomonolepis" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Neomonolepis</taxonomicName>
' clade.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="103" type="typification">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="103">Typification.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="103">
The type specimen lodged at GH contains several plants collected from different areas in California and almost all of them were collected after the description of 
<taxonomicName authority="H.A.Schrader, 1831" authorityName="A. Gray" authorityYear="1868" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Monolepis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Monolepis spathulata" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="spathulata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">Monolepis spathulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/20179569" author="Gray, A" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the American Academy of Arts and Sciences" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" pagination="327 - 401" refId="B17" refString="Gray, A, 1868. Characters of new plants of California and elsewhere, principally of those collected by H.N. Bolander in the State Geological Survey. Proceedings of the American Academy of Arts and Sciences 7: 327 - 401, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/20179569" title="Characters of new plants of California and elsewhere, principally of those collected by H. N. Bolander in the State Geological Survey." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/20179569" volume="7" year="1868">Gray 1868</bibRefCitation>
). The lectotype selected here (lower right-hand specimen on the GH00037208 sheet) is a part of original material cited in the protologue as &quot;Sierra Nevada, at Mono Pass, in loose soil, Bolander&quot; (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/20179569" author="Gray, A" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the American Academy of Arts and Sciences" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" pagination="327 - 401" refId="B17" refString="Gray, A, 1868. Characters of new plants of California and elsewhere, principally of those collected by H.N. Bolander in the State Geological Survey. Proceedings of the American Academy of Arts and Sciences 7: 327 - 401, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/20179569" title="Characters of new plants of California and elsewhere, principally of those collected by H. N. Bolander in the State Geological Survey." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/20179569" volume="7" year="1868">Gray 1868</bibRefCitation>
) and it is chosen in accordance with Art. 9 of ICN (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.12705/Code.2018" author="Turland, NJ" journalOrPublisher="11. KMK Press, Moscow" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" refId="B60" refString="Turland, NJ, Wiersema, JH, Barrie, FR, Greuter, W, Hawksworth, DL, Herendeen, PS, Knapp, S, Kusber, WH, Li, DZ, Marhold, K, May, TW, McNeill, J, Monro, AM, Prado, J, Price, MJ, Smith, GF, 2018. (2018) International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code): Adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Vegetabile 159. Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashuetten. https://doi.org/10.12705/Code.2018" title="(2018) International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code): Adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Vegetabile 159. Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashuetten." url="https://doi.org/10.12705/Code.2018" year="2018">Turland et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
). The description of the species is consistent with the image of the lectotype. 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/20179569" author="Gray, A" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the American Academy of Arts and Sciences" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" pagination="327 - 401" refId="B17" refString="Gray, A, 1868. Characters of new plants of California and elsewhere, principally of those collected by H.N. Bolander in the State Geological Survey. Proceedings of the American Academy of Arts and Sciences 7: 327 - 401, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/20179569" title="Characters of new plants of California and elsewhere, principally of those collected by H. N. Bolander in the State Geological Survey." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/20179569" volume="7" year="1868">Gray (1868)</bibRefCitation>
also noted that the seeds of 
<taxonomicName authority="H.A.Schrader, 1831" authorityName="A. Gray" authorityYear="1868" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Monolepis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Monolepis spathulata" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="spathulata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">Monolepis spathulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are notably smaller than those of 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. chenopodioides" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" rank="species" species="chenopodioides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">M. chenopodioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[= 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Blitum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Blitum nuttallianum" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nuttallianum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">Blitum nuttallianum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
]. The small seed dimensions of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Neomonolepis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Neomonolepis spathulata" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="spathulata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">Neomonolepis spathulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(0.4 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.3 mm) are similar to those observed in many Australian 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Dysphania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Dysphania" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">Dysphania</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Wilson, PG" editor="George, AS" journalOrPublisher="4. Australian Government Publishing Service, Canberra" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" pagination="81 - 317" refId="B67" refString="Wilson, PG, 1984. Chenopodiaceae. In: George, AS, Ed., Flora of Australia, Vol. 4. Australian Government Publishing Service, Canberra: 81 - 317" title="Chenopodiaceae." volumeTitle="Flora of Australia, Vol." year="1984">Wilson 1984</bibRefCitation>
sub 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Chenopodiaceae" genus="Chenopodium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Chenopodium" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">Chenopodium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Sukhorukov, AP" journalOrPublisher="Bioinformatics" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" refId="B51" refString="Sukhorukov, AP, 2014. The carpology of the Chenopodiaceae with reference to the phylogeny, systematics and diagnostics of its representatives. Grif &amp; Co., Tula. [in Russian with English summary]" title="The carpology of the Chenopodiaceae with reference to the phylogeny, systematics and diagnostics of its representatives. Grif &amp; Co., Tula. [in Russian with English summary]" year="2014">Sukhorukov 2014</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
